Problem Statement

Healthcare organizations often rely on manual or paper-based systems to manage patient information, appointments, prescriptions, and medical records. These traditional methods are time-consuming, prone to human errors, and can result in data loss or duplication. Patients may experience difficulties in booking appointments, accessing medical records, and tracking their treatment history. Similarly, doctors and hospital staff face challenges in maintaining accurate records and providing timely healthcare services.

To overcome these issues, there is a need for a centralized and digital healthcare management system that can securely store patient information, streamline appointment scheduling, manage prescriptions, and provide easy access to medical records. The proposed MediTrack – Smart Healthcare Management System aims to improve the efficiency, accuracy, and accessibility of healthcare services through a user-friendly web-based platform.

Objectives

To digitize patient and medical record management.

To simplify appointment booking and scheduling.

To maintain accurate and secure healthcare data.

To reduce paperwork and manual errors.

To provide quick access to patient information and medical history.

To improve communication between patients and healthcare providers.


Expected Outcome

The system will provide a secure, reliable, and efficient platform for managing healthcare information, helping both patients and healthcare professionals save time, reduce errors, and improve the overall quality of healthcare services.
